07/08/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Croatian Foreign Ministry sent a diplomatic note to Slovenia Wednesday (6 August) in response to questions about possible ecological damage to the Adriatic Sea at the Croatian economic zone near the border with Slovenia. The ministry said that all Croatia's activities in the region are harmonised with the EU standards for protection of the environment. The letter pledged that the country would observe all standards and practices of good neighbour relations.
In related news, Croatian Assistant Foreign Minister Darko Bekic met Slovene Ambassador to Croatia Petar Vekes on Wednesday to discuss the issue of the Adriatic economic zone's environmental impact. The two officials said their countries would find ways to resolve existing problems concerning fishing and environmental protection in the zone. (HINA - 06/08/03)
